SAP Description: BTTM LINE BNFTS & COMP WEB NWL 1Y
TITLE: Hazardous Materials Label Packs
SUBHEAD: Assortments for replacing missing or damaged labels
PDP DESCRIPTION:
• Labels meet the requirements of 49 CFR Part 172(E)
  • This set of hazardous materials labels contains 50 each of 14 different hazmat warning labels; you get a total of 700 DOT-required labels.  Also included in the set are charts which feature full-color illustrations of hazardous materials warning labels required by the DOT.
  • The kit includes the following labels and charts:
    • 50 - Non-Flammable Gas (4" x 4")
    • 50 - Flammable Solid (4" x 4")
    • 50 - Corrosive (4" x 4")
    • 50 - Oxidizer (4" x 4")
    • 50 - Radioactive I (4" x 4")
    • 50 - Radioactive III (4" x 4")
    • 50 - Dangerous When Wet (4" x 4")
    • 50 - Empty (6" x 6")
    • 50 - Oxygen (4" x 4")
    • 50 - Empty Container Warning Label (6" x 6")
    • 50 - Infectious Substance (4" x 4")
    • 50 - Miscellaneous DG Class 9 (4" x 4")
    • 50 - Inhalation Hazard Class 6
    • 50 - Poison, PG III, Class 6
    • 5 - HazMat Labeling Charts (8-1/2" x 11")
    • 5 - HazMat Load and Segregation Charts (8-1/2" x 11")
    • 1 - HazMat Label Chart w/adhesive (8-1/2" x 11")
